    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-21T08:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-21T08:44:00-05:00" n="419"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7962/32½: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Walton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-21T13:00:00-00:44"
                            >January 21, 1942—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 23—12:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. If report is true that Pan American engineers have been instructed to have
                    Roberts Field in readiness for landing of bombers by January 26, Legation
                    suggests that Liberian Government be approached for necessary permission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
